        <m>\mathbf{x}, \mathbf{y}\in S</m> so that <m>\mathbf{e}\in \{t\cdot \mathbf{x}+(1-t)\cdot \mathbf{y} : t\in (0,1)\}</m>.
        <!--
        TYPO
        should be (0,1)
        include corner point
        Fixed
        -->
      </p>
      <p>
        In other words, <m>\mathbf{e}</m> does not lie on any nontrivial line segment contained in <m>S</m>.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </definition>

